I enjoyed this movie though it was a little hard to follow. My friend is cousin to one of the actresses and everyone in the film is a novice to my knowledge. Based on this premise the acting is well done. The movie does hiccup on what exactly it is meant to convey. I am not really sure what some of the relationships are supposed to convey but movie was enjoyable nonetheless.

This film is going to require the viewer to pay attention. It helps a little to read the synopsis of what the film is about because it doesn't go out of its way to explain what the main character is doing in Iowa up front. I thought it was pretty good. There are some points where you are left to insert your own imagination of what the characters are thinking while there is no dialogue. If you are not paying attention to what is going on then it can become disjointed during those times. It was worth the rental if you are into films that require viewer engagement.

This was an enjoyable film.  The acting was surprisingly good and it was emotionally stimulating for me.  It's a story about a young girl still exploring her sexuality and she runs into a few characters along the way, some good, some not so good.  You wouldn't be wasting your time watching this.

I wasn't going to rate it, but when I read the reviews, I was disappointed and thought to jump in...I really like it. True, it is slow and at times, needs a few lines of script (especially  after Jennifer's 4 minutes teary eyed monologue), but there is softness that is really pleasing. The title could have been Bumble Love and be closer to the actual emotions.

This rating doesn't do justice by this film. The simplicity of the film and emotional connection are perfect. Not to mention its a film that sheds light on an important current issue. (If you end up here for some reason, definitely give it a go)

I really wanted to give it more stars but it was very hard not to fall asleep or at the very least lose a bit of interest in the story. I don't mind movies that move slow but this moved VERY slowly. It's worth a watch if you have nothing else to do. I didn't hate it, it had a lot of potential but so many empty scenes were dragged out while the ones they should have spent more time on were rushed. Not the worst movie I have seen though.
